Common.Strapline.Common.Text: OCCUPY / INVEST / DEVELOP IN BELCONNEN TOWN CENTRE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This prime unit on the corner of Josephson Street and Luxton Street provides a superb branding and retail opportunity for any business.

While location convenience will attract walk-in customers for a retail operation, the spacious units will also suit professionals such as lawyers, architects and financial planners. There are 12 car parks on site. 

If required, the property can be split into two sizable units. The unit includes offices, meeting and boardrooms, kitchen, toilets and rear roller door access to storage area. 

For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact CBRE.

*Approx.

Available for lease is a never before occupied commercial/retail unit, situated on the ground floor of the LINQ Apartments.  Located centrally in Belconnen across the road from CISAC and in close proximity to the bus interchange, Belconnen Mall and various amenity including restaurants and fast food outlets, this is a fantastic opportunity for a range of users.

The unit features the following;
- Extensive glass shopfront
- Excellent natural light
- High ceilings
- Bi-fold doors
- Unisex toilet
- NBN

Do not miss out on this incredible opportunity to secure this location. For further information or to arrange an inspection please contact CBRE.

Northpoint Plaza, 8 Chandler Street Belconnen ACT is offered for sale exclusively by CBRE.

The key investment highlights for the property are:

- 4,392sqm NLA commercial asset with multiple value-add strategies 
- Multi-tenanted asset providing holding income
- Potential to increase returns and lease expiry profile
- 75% occupied with major tenant being Commonwealth of Australia (Centrelink) who occupy 16% of the NLA
- Fully leased net income $1,010,668 p.a (approx.)
- Refurbishment and reposition opportunity
- Possible long term prime residential redevelopment (subject to DA)
- 1.5-star NABERS Energy Rating
- 55 basement car parks

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: COMPELLING VALUE-ADD OPPORTUNITY IN NATIONAL CAPITAL

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
First floor office accommodation in an attractive lakeside building known as 'The Promenade'. The building is situated on Emu Bank, located on the foreshore of Lake Ginninderra and on the fringe of the Belconnen Town Centre.  Emu Bank has developed with a mixture of high rise residential buildings and a number of restaurant outlets, together with two storey professional offices.  The Central Business District of the National Capital, Civic, is approximately 10 kilometres distant, whilst the Belconnen Town Centre, a major employment and retailing centre is within easy walking distance.

For further information or to arrange for an inspection, please contact the nominated representatives of CB Richard Ellis, Canberra.
